The actual monk fights (Battle Stuff) is very simple to complete, however when it takes 40 hours to get raster, 15 hours for targin, 20 hours for the Drolvarg Pawbuster, 6 or 7 times with a full group at the Bridgekeeper area of chardok<br>
<br>
As for the rogue epic... I know it's much more common than the mage one, but certain things like phinny robes, 8 hour ground spawns, etc are bottlenecks in that one...<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It grants the monk 40% haste which stacks with spell and item haste.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You could call the monk epic &quot;song&quot; haste I suppose, but it does not stack with spells like alacrity, swift like the wind, anya's quickening, etc. The ONLY songs which stack with spell haste are Melody and Composition of Erjav, and Battlecry and Warsong of the Vah Shir.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Shaman I know with their epic and jbb can solo mobs using almost no mana, stuff that would be tough for us even with epic.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I have my epic. When I solo, I have 2 choices. Root/Rot (Root, epic dot, and stack poison/disease) or Battlebear (buff myself out the wazoo, slow the mob (250 mana) and JBB with my pet.<br>
<br>
Now I don't have torpor. Anything that has either over 8000 hit points or so, or hits for more than 135 is too tough for me to solo this way. though I don't use too much mana, I end up losing a lot of health and spend mana healing myself.  I would agree that the shaman epic is a great item. it doesn't break root, it's fairly quick to deal damage... but to simply root and epic something to death takes forever, and if you JBB you'd probably end more mana trying to root it than you'd spend on dots in the first place <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  it's a tool, not a magic wand.<br>
<br>
The mage pet on the other hand, is an incredible item, and unique in several aspects. It's the only epic you can have readily available on a corpse run (unless you banked yours for some reason.) it's the only epic you can bring along should you change servers. Look at it this way, your epic could shoot leaves everywhere, look like a duck, or have no particle effect at all (*sniff* rogue?) at least it looks cool =P <p><table align="center" border="5" style="border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial; color: #8888FF; bordercolor="#9999FF" bordercolorlight="#5555FF" bordercolordark="#000088"><tr><td align="center" bgcolor="#000000"><IMG SRC="http://www.grizlorspics.iwarp.com/tunaresux.jpg"></FONT></td><td bgcolor="#000000" align="center"><B><FONT COLOR="#5555FF">My Toons:</B><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45358" target="_blank"><b> </FONT><FONT COLOR="#CDDFF">Grizlor</a></B></FONT> Shaman<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48124" target="_blank"><B><FONT COLOR="#CDDFF">Bigbrawler</a></B></FONT> Monk<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=56772" target="_blank"><B><FONT COLOR="#CDDFF">Ellone</a></B></FONT> Rogue<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=177859" target="_blank"><B><FONT COLOR="#CDDFF">Gobobtik</a></B></FONT> Beastlord<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=152243" target="_blank"><B><FONT COLOR="#CDDFF">Xylophone</a></B></FONT> Bard</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxisrene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xisrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 1:23:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://xisrene.freewebspace.com/images/xisrenep.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage epic designer was sadistic</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
As for the Monk Epic.. there are better haste items for the Monk.. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You miss the point of why the monk epic is so awesome. <br>
<br>
First, it's spell haste. That means it stacks with item haste. A soloing monk could hit the haste cap all by his lonesome. How many spell haste items are there in the game?<br>
<br>
Second, it's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not a weapon</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. It's gloves. Many monks on monkly business are of the opinion that there are no better monk gloves even to the high end game.<br>
<br>
Bard epic drastically changes the way they play their game. Using instruments suddenly becomes optional rather than mandatory. Not to mention suddenly being able to twist instrument only songs while meleeing without having to swap items. Party spell haste proc ain't too shabby either.<br>
<br>
As far as I know, the mage epic is the only one that is used as an argument for balancing. &quot;Well, with the epic pet a mage can blah, blah, blah&quot;.<br>
<br>
My big problem with the mage epic quest is that it makes no sense. We don't get an interesting storyline like other classes. We get some hackneyed, disjointed account of some jerk named Magi'Kot whose claim to fame was apparently being a putz. We have to journey far and wide collecting items on a &quot;grocery list&quot; that have absolutely nothing to do with being either a master of elements or of summoning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usalafia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salafia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(5/27/02 4:22:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage epic designer was sadistic</span><hr size=1> One other fact that was over looked is that OUR epic being so damaging, we get penalized for it. We must out damage it or we get half exp. SO now we have this hard hitting pet who makes it even harder to out damage. I am not going to bring up all the old rants about warriors and their swords and monks and their haste and how they are not penalized but its not fair IMO. I think IF you ever obtain your epic and SINCE its a spell you should NOT have to out damage it. NOW that would be almost worth the 200 hours I put in so far towards my epic.  Hell I could start a Shaman today and get his epic before my Mage, now that is sad.<br>
